{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_25","type":"agent_message","text":"Human intervention needed\n\nThe automated job failed for `xalan:xalan:2.7.3`, but preserved work is available here: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-4115-fails-java-run-xalan-xalan-2.7.3-d1fb8a7e\n\nThe most likely failing stage was the initial Java run (`:test` under `:tckTest`). `human-intervention-logs/xalan:xalan:2.7.3/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-02T16-21-53-065050Z.log` and `human-intervention-logs/xalan:xalan:2.7.3/fix-java-run-fail/pi-generation-2026-05-02T16-25-59-345535Z.log` show `XalanTest` failing with `NoClassDefFoundError` / `ClassNotFoundException` for `org.apache.xml.serializer.SerializerTrace` and `org.apache.xml.serializer.OutputPropertiesFactory`, which then bubbles up as `Execution failed for task ':test'` and `:tckTest`. The preserved diff adds `testRuntimeOnly \"xalan:serializer:$libraryVersion\"` in `tests/src/xalan/xalan/2.7.3/build.gradle`, which is the most likely fix for that stage.\n\nAfter that, native verification still needed metadata. `human-intervention-logs/xalan:xalan:2.7.3/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-02T16-33-03-126301Z.log` shows intermediate native failures with `MissingResourceException` for `org.apache.xml.res.XMLErrorResources` and `org.apache.xml.serializer.utils.SerializerMessages`, and `human-intervention-logs/xalan:xalan:2.7.3/metadata-fix/codex.log` says the preserved work restored a new `metadata/xalan/xalan/2.7.3/reachability-metadata.json` from the working 2.7.0 baseline with 2.7.3-specific `SecuritySupport` conditions. Later reruns passed in `human-intervention-logs/xalan:xalan:2.7.3/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-02T16-36-32-519972Z.log`, `human-intervention-logs/xalan:xalan:2.7.3/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-02T16-37-15-768242Z.log`, and `human-intervention-logs/xalan:xalan:2.7.3/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-02T16-38-01-557988Z.log`, so the workflow appears to have produced a viable candidate fix even though the overall run still ended as `job_failed`. Metrics were written, but `stats/xalan/xalan/2.7.3/stats.json` reports `dynamicAccess: N/A`.\n\nPlease:\n1. Review the preserved branch diff, especially `tests/src/xalan/xalan/2.7.3/build.gradle` and the new `metadata/xalan/xalan/2.7.3/reachability-metadata.json`, to confirm the runtime dependency addition and large metadata restoration are acceptable.\n2. Re-run `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=xalan:xalan:2.7.3` from the preserved branch and spot-check `./gradlew checkMetadataFiles -Pcoordinates=xalan:xalan:2.7.3`.\n3. If the preserved metadata change is too broad, trim `metadata/xalan/xalan/2.7.3/reachability-metadata.json` to the minimal required entries and rerun the same verification."}}
